  "Name": "PartFSpaceRules_UK_Dwellings_MVHR",
  "Version": "2.0",
  "Notes": [
    "For domestic MVHR under Approved Document F, use the whole-dwelling ventilation rate as the greater of the bedroom-based rate and 0.3 l/s per m2 internal floor area.",
    "Supply is assigned to habitable rooms.",
    "Extract is assigned to wet rooms.",
    "Transfer spaces normally have no terminal.",
    "Void/open-to-below spaces should normally be excluded from the floor area check.",
    "Living rooms should not automatically be treated as kitchens. Only classify as LivingKitchen where the room is clearly open-plan and contains the cooking function, or when a higher-level dwelling rule determines that the main living space includes the kitchen.",
    "If the final whole-dwelling rate is greater than the sum of wet-room minimums, recalculate the final supply and extract terminal flow rates so that total supply and total extract both match the final system rate.",
    "Wet-room minimum extract rates are minimum values only. Final calculated extract rates may be higher."
  ],
  "WholeDwellingRates_Lps": {
    "Studio": 19,
    "1": 19,
    "2": 25,
    "3": 31,
    "4": 37,
    "5": 43,
    "IncrementAbove5": 6,
    "AreaRate_LpsPerM2": 0.3
